==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saphenous
<hw>Sa*phe"nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
manifest.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Manifest; --
applied to the two principal superficial veins of the lower limb of
man.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of, pertaining to, or in the region of, the
saphenous veins; <as>as, the <ex>saphenous</ex> nerves; the
<ex>saphenous</ex> opening, an opening in the broad fascia of the thigh
through which the internal saphenous vein passes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

